<br>
Depending on why they are taking them can lead to several reactions. There are all kinds of legit reasons to take anti-depressants... chronic depression, bipolar disorder, obsessive compulsive disorder, social anxiety disorder, seasonal affective disorder (sp?)... <br>
<br>
Someone who is bipolar taking meds will not be on such a &quot;roller coaster&quot;. Someone who is chronically depressed will have a more positive outlook on life in general. Someone who has OCD will calm down about their routines, someone who has social anxiety will feel more comfortable in public places.<br>
<br>
You also have to take into consideration whether or not they have found, or are trying to find the right drug/dose. The wrong meds can turn a person into a &quot;stranger&quot; (acts like someone you've never met), too high of a dose can do the same thing. <br>
<br>
Though I will tell you this... you are looking for a way to tell if someone is taking medication. I would suggest before you do anything else, simply ask them. It has been my experience that if someone is taking meds for a legit reason, they will be happy to talk about it with you, for a number of reasons... they feel good about taking a step to improve their life, they need input from people around them every day to judge their reaction to meds.<br>
<br>
Granted this all changes if you suspect they are taking them as a means of &quot;getting high&quot;... and if you suspect that, then you're probably right. Your instincts are already telling you this person is acting different, and your intuition tells you its because of some mood altering drug.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 2:50:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Anti-Depressants and spotting them from a mile away</span><hr size=1> Basically, it's a ladyfriend I'm trying to figure out.<br>
