My personal experience is with Manic Depression, both from myself and my father. While the term &quot;manic depression&quot; is generally defined as &quot;extreme highs and extreme lows&quot;. This is not actually the case. For me, manic depression means I feel &quot;normal&quot; for a while, and in the blink of an eye (literally) I can be absolutely hopeless. For my dad, that his manic depression mean that he would be VERY angry one minute, and &quot;didnt give a shit&quot; the next. <br>
Depression doesnt always mean someone is sad. More often than not, a depressed person will tell you they are not sad. They just have no hope of ever being happy. There is a difference. 'Cause if you're sad, there's something you're sad about, and that something can usually be pinpointed and eventually fixed... and when you're depressed you're sad about everything and nothing at the same time. Its not about sitting in the dark room crying because &lt;insert horrific tragedy here&gt; its about sitting in a well lit room watching your family and friends meander around doing thier daily normal things with a smile on their face, and you cant think of one single thing to smile for ... cause its all tainted by something dark.<br>
They are right about being masters of deception <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Cause it feels like no one can do anything about it, so why bother them with your problems. You dont want to ruin the smiles of these people, just cause you cant find one... that would be terrible, cause you dont want ANYONE else to feel the way you do... so why ruin them by telling them you're miserable.<br>
<br>
&quot;Happy Pills&quot; are not that. They dont make you smile, or give you a reason to smile, or even make you feel like smiling... They give you the ability to take a deep breath and only see the puzzle piece you're working on at that moment, rather than the three million random peices you have left, and the big empty space on the table that you're expected to fill with a picture, put together by all these pieces. Anti-depressants, (oh yeah um in my personal experience hehehe forgot that I am not the whole world /grin) give you the ability to take a step, even if it is a baby step... then you realize that the step wasnt so hard, so you can take the next one and the one after that... then you've been taking steps for so long you stop to turn around and realize you've walked around the block... and it was okay. It wasnt horrible, and it was kinda easy cause you did it a step at a time, at your own pace. They just make everything a little bit more bearable, so you can do it... ya might not be &quot;happy&quot; about it but you're sure as hell not hopeless....<br>
<br>
One more thing, then I'll stop <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
People who are depressed, CAN NOT &quot;flip a switch&quot; and be happy. There is something chemically wrong with the mechanisms in their brain (not thier mind) and it cant be done. The same way someone with a broken leg cant just &quot;decide&quot; to get up and walk. So if you're trying to help, dont bring flowers and ballons and big grin to say hey lets go &lt;insert super fun thing here&gt; 'cause it wont do any good. They will put on thier mask, cause doing the thing will make YOU happy and you dont have to know how they really feel. Eventually (and hopefully) the depressed person will figure out they need help, and if the avenues have been laid in place, they will ask for it. Your job (as the friend/loved one of someone you know needs help) is to say &quot;im here when you need me to be&quot;. And as sucky as it is to watch them suffer, that has to be good enough for you. &quot;Fixing it&quot; wont work unless the depressed person wants to fix themselves. <br>
<br>
(This is NOT in anyway to say if you know someone who is suicidal that you shouldnt do something about it. Someone who going to physically harm themselves, needs help as quick as possible, regardless of whether or not they want it.)<br>
